  {q:"Is SCHD or VYM better?",a:"SCHD has outperformed VYM on nearly every metric: higher yield (3.4% vs 2.8%), better 5-year returns (12.1% vs 10.8%), and identical expense ratio (0.06%). SCHD screens for dividend quality and cash flow, while VYM simply targets high-yield stocks. VYM's advantage is broader diversification (440 vs 104 holdings), but for most investors SCHD is the stronger choice."},
  {q:"What is the difference between dividend growth and high yield ETFs?",a:"Dividend growth ETFs (VIG, DGRO) buy companies that consistently raise dividends — they yield less now (1.7-2.2%) but income grows each year and total returns are higher. High yield ETFs (VYM, HDV, SPYD) maximize current income (2.8-4.5%) from mature companies. Historically, dividend growth strategies deliver better total returns over 10+ year periods."},
